
The RPM package name "otop-0.6-4.el7.noarch.rpm" follows standard RPM naming conventions. 

``` bash
name-version-release.architecture.rpm
```

Where:
- `otop`: Package name
- `0.6`: Version number
- `4`: Release number
- `el7`: Distribution tag (Enterprise Linux 7, for RHEL/CentOS 7)
- `noarch`: Architecture (architecture-independent)
- `.rpm`: File extension indicating RPM package format

This specific package is an architecture-independent application
(indicated by "noarch") built for EL7-based distributions.
